The paper is about improving Statistical Machine Translation (SMT) using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new features based on neural networks and applies multitask learning, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of tensor layers, which are commonly used in neural networks for computer vision (CV), making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) possible sub-categories.
